title: Introduction to curatoR
text: curatoR designed help biologists pull data GBIF curate quickly. GBIF data messy, manually curating time consuming. curatoR allows biologists use existing Expert Curated Dataset (ECD) filter GBIF data easily update ECD.

title: Introduction to curatoR
text: first step workflow done using “occ_since” function allows user pull GBIF data certain taxon since certain date. function defaults pulling Carex data since June 2021. Note function defaults pulling data (1,000,000 occurrences) since date, step can quite slow.

text: coming flagging functions, necessary continents labeled occurrence. ECD country code column named differently default, specify name column.

title: Introduction to curatoR
text: Next, species-continent combination, can build convex hull (species 3 different continents 3 separate convex hulls) flag species occur outside convex hulls.
code: flagged <- flag_convex_hull(flagged, ECD) summary(flagged) #>     .val     .equ     .zer     .cap     .cen     .sea     .otl     .gbf  #>        0        0        0       14        0       53       30        0  #>    .inst .summary .country    .hull  #>        0      255       88      102

title: Introduction to curatoR
text: Next, species-continent combination, flag occurrences species 2 standard deviations center distribution.
code: flagged <- flag_distance(flagged, ECD) summary(flagged) #>     .val     .equ     .zer     .cap     .cen     .sea     .otl     .gbf  #>        0        0        0       14        0       53       30        0  #>    .inst .summary .country    .hull    .dist  #>        0      263       88      102       27

title: Curate biological datasets
text: goal curatoR provide accessible way biologists curate biological datasets. Specifically, package provides functions flag suspicious observations based location, name, species. also provides easy way map observations.

title: Curate biological datasets
text: can install development version curator GitHub :
code: # install.packages("devtools") devtools::install_github("matthewbradley22/curator")

title: Curate biological datasets
text: depth example curatoR package, visit https://matthewbradley22.github.io/curator/

title: Curate biological datasets
text: basic example retriving data gbif, flagging CoordinateCleaner (flag_data), flagging species names data occur example ECD provided package (flag_names). column names begin period (seen summary(flags) ) indicate number observations certain flag. flagged can map data color presence type flags, seen .
code: library(curator)  #Retrieve data with rgbig::occ_search and pass to CoordinateCleaner::clean_coordinates data = occ_since(numObs = 500) flags = flag_data(data) #Flag names that do not occur in ECD flags = flag_names(flags, curator::ECD) summary(flags) #>     .val     .equ     .zer     .cap     .cen     .sea     .otl     .gbf  #>        0        0        0        5        0       35       10        0  #>    .inst .summary    .name  #>        0       53        6
